TopicTitle: KSP "Dying On Top of the World" tribute to 1.0 - Video released

Articles.Content:
Thank you so much SQUAD and you guys on the forum. It's been a pleasure making videos and sharing stories with you all. This video has been quite the eye opener into the past. ![:)](//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif)

**Dying On Top of the World**

**Thank you SQUAD!**

Avera9eJoe out.

**Edited <time datetime="2015-03-13T15:40:33Z" title="03/13/2015 03:40  PM" data-short="9 yr">March 13, 2015</time> by inigma**
Awesome videos and pictures guys! I've gotten great results so far ![:)](//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif)

This is the oldest album I could find on imgur (from about 2 years ago - not sure which update this was but I am guessing 0.19 or so, since it has EVA, but definitely before the addition of unmanned probes). All of my in-system screenshots are from after 0.18, and all around the same time period. There are no captions, but I think it's pretty straightforward as a mission to Duna. The fun part was on the way back, I ran out of fuel and hand to make highly strategic use of gravity assists and my very limited RCS fuel to get my kerbals home.

> [Javascript is disabled. View full album](//imgur.com/a/vh31D)

Cheers, and best of luck on your project!
